    "description": {
      "value": "<p>The light of dawn shines down on a location you specify within range. Until the spell ends, a 30-foot-radius, 40-foot-high cylinder of bright light glimmers there. This light is sunlight. Creatures, such as specters, wraiths, and will-o'-wisps within the cylinder cannot benefit from incorporeal movement.</p><p>When the cylinder appears, each creature in it must make a [[/save Constitution]] saving throw, taking [[/r 4d10]] radiant damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. A creature must also make this saving throw whenever it ends its turn in the cylinder.</p><p>If you're within 60 feet of the cylinder, you can move it up to 60 feet as a Bonus Action on your turn.</p><p><strong>Using a Higher-Level Spell Slot.</strong> The damage increases by 1d10 for each spell slot level above 5.</p>",
